02834  * ======== xdc.runtime.System TEMPLATE ========
02835  */
02836 
02837 
02838 #include <xdc/std.h>
02839 #include <limits.h>
02840 #include <xdc/runtime/Types.h>
02841 #include <xdc/runtime/Text.h>
02842 #include <xdc/runtime/Assert.h>
02843 
02844 /*
02845  *  ======== System_printfExtend__I ========
02846  *  This function processes optional extended formats of printf.
02847  *  
02848  *  It returns the number of characters added to the result.
02849  *
02850  *  Precision (maximum string length) is not supported for %$S.
02851  *
02852  *  Right-justified (which is default) minimum width is not supported
02853  *  for %$L, %$S, or %$F.
02854  */
02855 Int xdc_runtime_System_printfExtend__I(Char **pbuf, Char **pfmt, 
02856     VaList *pva, xdc_runtime_System_ParseData *parse)
02857 {
02858     Char    *fmt = *pfmt;
02859     Int     res;
02860     Char    c;
02861     Bool    found = FALSE;
02862     
02863     /* 
02864      * Create a local variable 'va' to ensure that the dereference of
02865      * pva only occurs once.
02866      */
02867     va_list va = *pva;
02868     
02869     res = 0;
02870 
02871     c = *fmt++;
02872     *pfmt = *pfmt + 1;
02873 
02874     if (c == 'f') {
02875         Double d, tmp;
02876         ULong  fract;
02877         Int    negative;
02878 
02879 
02880         if (parse->aFlag) {
02881             xdc_runtime_Assert_isTrue((sizeof(Float) <= sizeof(IArg)), 
02882                 xdc_runtime_System_A_cannotFitIntoArg);
02883 
02884             d = argToFloat(va_arg(va, IArg));
02885         }
02886         else {
02887             d = va_arg(va, double);
02888         }
02889 
02890         if (d < 0.0) {
02891             d = -d;
02892             negative = TRUE;
02893             parse->zpad--;
02894         }
02895         else {
02896             negative = FALSE;
02897         }
02898 
02899         /*
02900          * output (error) if we can't print correct value
02901          */
02902         if (d > (double) LONG_MAX) {
02903             parse->ptr = "(error)";
02904             parse->len = 7;                /* strlen("(error)"); */
02905             goto end;
02906         }
02907 
02908         /* Assumes four digits after decimal point. We are using a temporary
02909          * double variable to force double-precision computations without 
02910          * using --fp_mode=strict flag. See the description of that flag in
02911          * the compiler's doc for a further explanation.
02912          */
02913         tmp = (d - (Long)d) * 1e4;
02914         fract = (ULong)tmp;
02915 
02916         parse->ptr = xdc_runtime_System_formatNum__I(parse->end, fract, 4, 10);
02917         *(--parse->ptr) = '.';
02918 
02919 #if 0
02920         /* eliminate trailing zeros */
02921         do {
02922         } while (*(--parse->end) == '0');
02923         ++parse->end;
02924         parse->len = parse->end - parse->ptr;
02925 #endif
02926 
02927         /* format integer part (right to left!) */
02928         parse->ptr = xdc_runtime_System_formatNum__I(parse->ptr,
02929             (Long)d, parse->zpad - parse->len, 10);
02930         if (negative) {
02931             *(--parse->ptr) = '-';
02932         }
02933 
02934         parse->len = parse->end - parse->ptr;
02935         found = TRUE;
02936     }
02937 
02938     if (found == FALSE) {
02939         /* other character (like %) copy to output */
02940         *(parse->ptr) = c;
02941         parse->len = 1;
02942     }
02943 
02944     /*
02945      * Before returning, we must update the value of pva. We use a label here
02946      * so that all return points will go through this update.
02947      * The 'goto end' is here to ensure that there is always a reference to the
02948      * label (to avoid the compiler complaining). 
02949      */
02950     goto end; 
02951 end:
02952     *pva = va;
02953     return (res);
02954 }

03214 #if defined(__ti__)
03215 
03216 #include <xdc/std.h>
03217 
03218 #include <xdc/runtime/Memory.h>
03219 #include <xdc/runtime/Error.h>
03220 #include <stdlib.h>
03221 #include <string.h>
03222 
03223 /* malloc header */
03224 typedef struct Header {
03225     Ptr   actualBuf;
03226     SizeT size;
03227 } Header;
03228 
03229 #pragma FUNC_EXT_CALLED(malloc);
03230 #pragma FUNC_EXT_CALLED(memalign);
03231 #pragma FUNC_EXT_CALLED(free);
03232 #pragma FUNC_EXT_CALLED(calloc);
03233 #pragma FUNC_EXT_CALLED(realloc);
03234 
03235 /*
03236  *  ======== malloc ========
03237  */
03238 Void *malloc(SizeT size)
03239 {
03240     Header *packet;
03241     xdc_runtime_Error_Block eb;
03242 
03243     xdc_runtime_Error_init(&eb);
03244 
03245     if (size == 0) {
03246         return (NULL);
03247     }
03248 
03249     packet = (Header *)xdc_runtime_Memory_alloc(NULL,
03250         (SizeT)(size + sizeof(Header)), 0, &eb);
03251 
03252     if (packet == NULL) {
03253         return (NULL);
03254     }
03255 
03256     packet->actualBuf = (Ptr)packet;
03257     packet->size = size + sizeof(Header);
03258 
03259     return (packet + 1);
03260 }
03261 
03262 /*
03263  *  ======== memalign ========
03264  *  mirrors the memalign() function from the TI run-time library
03265  */
03266 Void *memalign(SizeT alignment, SizeT size)
03267 {
03268     Header                      *packet;
03269     Void                        *tmp;
03270     xdc_runtime_Error_Block     eb;
03271 
03272     xdc_runtime_Error_init(&eb);
03273 
03274     if (size == 0) {
03275         return (NULL);
03276     }
03277 
03278     /*
03279      * If alignment is not a power of two or is less than the minimum
03280      * alignment of malloc(), then simply return what malloc() returns.
03281      * (same as behaviour as RTS library's memalign())
03282      * Note: HeapMem's header is the same as this header after it is raised
03283      * to a power of 2.
03284      */
03285     if (alignment <= sizeof(Header) || (alignment & (alignment-1))) {
03286         return malloc(size);
03287     }
03288 
03289     /*
03290      * Allocate 'align + size' so that we have room for the 'packet'
03291      * and can return an aligned buffer.
03292      */
03293     tmp = xdc_runtime_Memory_alloc(NULL, alignment + size,
03294         (SizeT)alignment, &eb);
03295 
03296     if (tmp == NULL) {
03297         return (NULL);
03298     }
03299 
03300     packet = (Header *)((char *)tmp + alignment - sizeof(Header));
03301 
03302     packet->actualBuf = tmp;
03303     packet->size = size + sizeof(Header);
03304 
03305     return (packet + 1);
03306 }
03307 
03308 /*
03309  *  ======== calloc ========
03310  */
03311 Void *calloc(SizeT nmemb, SizeT size)
03312 {
03313     SizeT       nbytes;
03314     Ptr         retval;
03315 
03316     nbytes = nmemb * size;
03317 
03318     retval = malloc(nbytes);
03319     if (retval != NULL) {
03320         (Void)memset(retval, (Int)'\0', nbytes);
03321     }
03322 
03323     return (retval);
03324 }

03326 /*
03327  *  ======== free ========
03328  */
03329 Void free(Void *ptr)
03330 {
03331     Header      *packet;
03332 
03333     if (ptr != NULL) {
03334         packet = ((Header *)ptr) - 1;
03335 
03336         xdc_runtime_Memory_free(NULL, (Ptr)packet->actualBuf,
03337             (packet->size + ((char*)packet - (char*)packet->actualBuf)));
03338     }
03339 }
03340 
03341 /*
03342  *  ======== realloc ========
03343  */
03344 Void *realloc(Void *ptr, SizeT size)
03345 {
03346     Ptr         retval;
03347     Header      *packet;
03348     SizeT       oldSize;
03349 
03350     if (ptr == NULL) {
03351         retval = malloc(size);
03352     }
03353     else if (size == 0) {
03354         free(ptr);
03355         retval = NULL;
03356     }
03357     else {
03358         packet = (Header *)ptr - 1;
03359         retval = malloc(size);
03360         if (retval != NULL) {
03361             oldSize = packet->size - sizeof(Header);
03362             (Void)memcpy(retval, ptr, (size < oldSize) ? size : oldSize);
03363             free(ptr);
03364         }
03365     }
03366 
03367     return (retval);
03368 }
